#!/bin/sh
# Silent stub for OpenWrt's `uci` command. oxwrtd replaces UCI with
# TOML (see /etc/oxwrt.toml), but OpenWrt's shipped preinit /
# hotplug / firstboot scripts still shell out to `uci` for things
# like "read the hostname" or "set an interface up". Without a
# binary on $PATH those scripts log "uci: not found" (e.g. from
# /etc/preinit line 18) and either fail-open or noisily retry.
#
# Strategy: accept any args, print nothing, exit 0. The callers
# either use the output in a `$(...)` assignment (which gets empty
# string → falls back to default), or in a boolean check (which
# passes through). No caller we've observed relies on a specific
# non-empty value — if one surfaces later, special-case that key
# in this stub rather than shipping the full libuci binary.

exit 0
